<section class="section section--flush-top">
  <div class="faq-list">
    <details open><summary>What is genuinely live?</summary><div>Static pages are live by definition. Command's health and audit results are live only after the same-origin Worker returns a valid response. Fight Club and Swarm show the exact engine used for each completed run.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Are Arena matches real provider calls?</summary><div>No. The Arena is an editorial exhibition archive. Use Fight Club for current provider-aware comparisons.</div></details>
    <details><summary>What happens if a provider is not configured?</summary><div>The interface reports that state. If Workers AI is available, the Worker may use it as a labeled fallback. A curated demo is never substituted silently.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Where are API keys stored?</summary><div>Provider credentials belong in Cloudflare Worker secrets. They are not included in the repository, HTML, public configuration, health response, or browser storage.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Does Atlas ID sync between devices?</summary><div>No automatic account sync exists. Atlas ID is stored in the current browser. Export the JSON file and import it on another device if you want to move it.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Does Forge Atlas track visitors?</summary><div>The source does not load advertising or third-party analytics scripts. Hosting and security providers may still process request metadata needed to deliver and protect the site; see the Privacy page.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Can I purchase premium access?</summary><div>No. Paid access is paused. The site does not claim that a checkout is active and does not request transaction identifiers.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Is Command an admin panel?</summary><div>No. The public page contains health and audit tools only. It cannot deploy, roll back, promote, purge, or mutate production infrastructure.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Is Forge Atlas affiliated with model providers?</summary><div>No affiliation or endorsement is implied. Provider and model-family names remain trademarks of their respective owners.</div></details>
    <details><summary>Can I inspect or deploy the code?</summary><div>Yes. The repository includes the source tree, build commands, Worker contract, configuration examples, tests, and deployment notes. Real provider use still requires your own authorized server-side configuration.</div></details>
  </div>
</section>
